- Stay out of it.
- Darn.

823
00:53:12,090 --> 00:53:13,430
You wait and see.

824
00:53:13,430 --> 00:53:15,860
I'll see to it
that you lose your job.

825
00:53:15,860 --> 00:53:17,830
I'll come for your head,

826
00:53:17,830 --> 00:53:19,970
so just wait and see, you jerk.

827
00:53:19,970 --> 00:53:21,340
Honey, that's enough!

828
00:53:29,710 --> 00:53:31,180
Let's go home, honey.

829
00:53:31,850 --> 00:53:33,950
Please let go of him.
I'll take him home.

830
00:53:33,950 --> 00:53:34,980
Darn it.

831
00:53:36,920 --> 00:53:38,290
Ms. Jang?

832
00:53:42,190 --> 00:53:43,390
It's been a while.

833
00:53:55,970 --> 00:53:57,510
I'm sorry for the commotion.

834
00:53:58,110 --> 00:53:59,210
We'll get going.

835
00:53:59,310 --> 00:54:00,610
Honey, let's go.

836
00:54:01,380 --> 00:54:02,440
Darn.

837
00:54:03,080 --> 00:54:04,650
I'm way too angry to just walk away.

838
00:54:05,280 --> 00:54:07,250
- No!
- Watch out.

839
00:54:18,430 --> 00:54:19,890
Are you all right?

840
00:54:25,670 --> 00:54:28,170
Oh Beom Soo, hear me loud and clear.

841
00:54:28,670 --> 00:54:31,370
You'll pay
for going after my daughter.

842
00:54:31,770 --> 00:54:33,740
I'll end you.

843
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:41,020
I'm so sorry about this.

844
00:54:47,520 --> 00:54:50,060
What on earth just happened?

845
00:54:50,160 --> 00:54:51,890
How is it that this family
can't have a single day...

846
00:54:51,890 --> 00:54:53,630
of peace and quiet?

847
00:54:59,130 --> 00:55:00,200
Beom Soo.

848
00:55:03,100 --> 00:55:04,610
Is what he said true?

849
00:55:11,580 --> 00:55:13,520
Let me get this straight.

850
00:55:13,980 --> 00:55:16,180
Dokgo Tak's daughter...

851
00:55:16,250 --> 00:55:17,990
is one of your students,

852
00:55:19,120 --> 00:55:21,920
and she broke off her engagement
to be with you?

853
00:55:38,440 --> 00:55:39,840
Beom Soo, wait.

854
00:55:46,450 --> 00:55:49,580
Let's not do this out here
and take it inside.

855
00:56:35,900 --> 00:56:39,030
(Chairman Han Dong Seok)

856
00:56:39,030 --> 00:56:40,770
At 10 a.m., the signing ceremony...

857
00:56:40,770 --> 00:56:42,400
between Eagle Brewery
and Saman Mart...

858
00:56:42,400 --> 00:56:44,140
will take place
in the small conference room.

859
00:56:45,910 --> 00:56:48,040
Will you be attending as well?

860
00:56:48,910 --> 00:56:51,210
I don't think my presence
is required.

861
00:56:52,280 --> 00:56:53,820
Understood, sir.

862
00:57:33,190 --> 00:57:34,320
You may sit over here.

863
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:47,540
We're starting with 300 boxes
of Jang-Kwang Yakju every month,

864
00:57:48,040 --> 00:57:50,100
but I expect the number
to increase to 500 boxes...

865
00:57:50,100 --> 00:57:51,940
by the end of this year.

866
00:57:52,640 --> 00:57:55,640
We'll be ready
to handle the additional order.

867
00:57:56,610 --> 00:58:00,950
This year, we'll see
how well your yakju sells...

868
00:58:00,950 --> 00:58:04,050
as we build up a refrigerated fleet
before importing your makgeolli.

869
00:58:04,820 --> 00:58:06,290
Fermented rice wines...

870
00:58:06,290 --> 00:58:08,660
require special facilities
that take time to set up,

871
00:58:09,060 --> 00:58:11,060
but I don't think
that should be a problem.

872
00:58:11,160 --> 00:58:13,060
We've never exported
unrefined makgeolli,

873
00:58:13,060 --> 00:58:14,760
but we'll do some research
and prepare.

874
00:58:15,500 --> 00:58:16,500
Okay.

875
00:58:18,570 --> 00:58:20,340
Shall we begin, then?

876
00:58:20,670 --> 00:58:21,740
Yes.

877
00:58:42,490 --> 00:58:45,490
Are you ready? One, two, three.

878
00:58:49,260 --> 00:58:50,670
Good job.

879
00:58:50,830 --> 00:58:52,600
- Well done.
- Thank you.

880
00:58:54,040 --> 00:58:57,940
I agreed to meet Chairman Han
for tea after this.

881
00:58:59,270 --> 00:59:00,580
You should join us.

882
00:59:01,480 --> 00:59:02,780
Me too?

883
00:59:04,380 --> 00:59:07,020
This deal wouldn't have happened
without him.

884
00:59:07,180 --> 00:59:09,680
Shouldn't you thank him at least?

885
00:59:11,490 --> 00:59:12,790
Go ahead, CEO Ma.

886
00:59:12,790 --> 00:59:14,520
I'll wait in the lobby.

887
00:59:16,260 --> 00:59:17,290
Let's go.

888
00:59:18,030 --> 00:59:19,060
Shall we?

889
00:59:30,440 --> 00:59:32,870
The chairman will come
as soon as he's free.

890
00:59:33,140 --> 00:59:34,180
Okay.

891
00:59:37,050 --> 00:59:38,780
I need to take this.

892
00:59:38,850 --> 00:59:39,850
Sure.

893
00:59:58,100 --> 00:59:59,100
What's this?

894
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:01,070
What's what?

895
01:00:01,600 --> 01:00:04,610
What are you doing in my office
without an appointment?

896
01:00:05,770 --> 01:00:07,480
Saman Mart's CEO brought me here...

897
01:00:07,480 --> 01:00:09,610
to thank you for brokering our deal,

898
01:00:10,240 --> 01:00:12,580
but he just left to take a call.

899
01:00:12,780 --> 01:00:14,320
That's why I was alone.

900
01:00:18,450 --> 01:00:19,650
Chairman Han.

901
01:00:23,560 --> 01:00:25,430
What did I do that was so wrong?

902
01:00:27,600 --> 01:00:29,230
If you say you like me,

903
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:31,700
should I just accept it
and date you?

904
01:00:32,500 --> 01:00:34,340
- What?
- I asked you...

905
01:00:34,770 --> 01:00:37,010
to give me a month
to think about it.

906
01:00:37,310 --> 01:00:39,370
You practically forced me
to think...

907
01:00:39,470 --> 01:00:41,210
over just ten days.

908
01:00:41,980 --> 01:00:43,110
So for ten days,

909
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:46,680
I thought about it so much.
I felt like my head would explode.

910
01:00:48,020 --> 01:00:49,080
That time,

911
01:00:50,250 --> 01:00:51,890
those ten days...

912
01:00:52,350 --> 01:00:54,920
might have been long enough for you,

913
01:00:55,460 --> 01:00:58,460
but on top of your demand,
I had a mountain of problems...

914
01:00:58,460 --> 01:00:59,790
I had to solve...

915
01:00:59,860 --> 01:01:02,530
just to keep my brewery going.

916
01:01:02,730 --> 01:01:04,730
I barely had any time.

917
01:01:05,330 --> 01:01:08,370
So what? What is your point?

918
01:01:09,070 --> 01:01:11,710
I didn't have enough time
to determine how I felt,

919
01:01:12,210 --> 01:01:13,980
so I rejected you
because I was uncertain.

920
01:01:14,580 --> 01:01:16,110
Isn't it childish...

921
01:01:16,180 --> 01:01:18,450
to get ticked off
and stress me out like this?

922
01:01:19,180 --> 01:01:21,820
Who's ticked off? Me?

923
01:01:21,880 --> 01:01:23,890
Yes, you.

924
01:01:24,450 --> 01:01:27,260
Do you think my feelings for you...

925
01:01:27,720 --> 01:01:29,790
were just some childish stunt?

926
01:01:29,820 --> 01:01:32,060
What you're doing...

927
01:01:32,260 --> 01:01:34,100
seems childish to me.

928
01:01:34,160 --> 01:01:37,270
Don't call an ordinary man childish.

929
01:01:38,770 --> 01:01:42,200
I bet no one ever said no
or rejected you...

930
01:01:42,470 --> 01:01:44,070
in your life.

931
01:01:46,310 --> 01:01:47,640
You're the first.

932
01:01:48,380 --> 01:01:51,080
You got angry
because you didn't get your way,

933
01:01:51,380 --> 01:01:53,820
and you don't care
how anyone else feels, do you?

934
01:01:54,180 --> 01:01:55,980
Are you lecturing me?

935
01:01:56,150 --> 01:01:58,450
I'm telling you
how you made me feel recently.

936
01:01:59,320 --> 01:02:00,590
Okay, whatever.

937
01:02:03,390 --> 01:02:06,130
I hope you get your way
and live happily...

938
01:02:06,130 --> 01:02:07,500
with your brothers-in-law...

939
01:02:07,500 --> 01:02:09,930
and stir makgeolli
for the rest of your life.

940
01:02:11,530 --> 01:02:13,130
Are you cursing me?

941
01:02:13,200 --> 01:02:14,500
How is that a curse?

942
01:02:14,500 --> 01:02:16,770
Isn't that the life you want?

943
01:02:17,670 --> 01:02:18,710
Yes.

944
01:02:19,840 --> 01:02:20,880
I was...

945
01:02:21,640 --> 01:02:24,450
so confused about what I wanted.

946
01:02:24,810 --> 01:02:28,020
Hearing what you just said
cleared my mind.

947
01:02:29,450 --> 01:02:30,650
From now on,

948
01:02:31,320 --> 01:02:33,150
I'll do as you said.

949
01:02:33,790 --> 01:02:36,790
I'll live happily
with my brothers-in-law forever...

950
01:02:37,060 --> 01:02:39,930
and make and stir makgeolli.

951
01:02:41,030 --> 01:02:42,100
What?

952
01:02:43,330 --> 01:02:44,630
I got worried,

953
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:48,400
felt butterflies, and wondered...

954
01:02:49,840 --> 01:02:50,970
for no reason.

955
01:02:54,040 --> 01:02:56,610
Thank you for the nice memories.

956
01:03:48,700 --> 01:03:51,200
(For Eagle Brothers)

957
01:03:51,630 --> 01:03:54,370
She has a dreadful-looking face.

958
01:03:54,940 --> 01:03:56,070
She's not for you.

959
01:03:56,070 --> 01:03:58,370
- What?
- You know what your dad's like.

960
01:03:58,440 --> 01:04:00,340
You can't beat him.

961
01:04:00,680 --> 01:04:02,040
This is the worst.

962
01:04:02,310 --> 01:04:04,980
I never even dreamed
of this happening.

963
01:04:05,110 --> 01:04:07,180
Give me your home address.

964
01:04:07,350 --> 01:04:09,820
I should've figured out
how she really felt.

965
01:04:10,350 --> 01:04:11,690
I was too rash.

966
01:04:12,390 --> 01:04:14,060
You were struggling,

967
01:04:14,590 --> 01:04:16,460
and I get all that now.

968
01:04:16,620 --> 01:04:19,730
You just have to watch what I do
from now on.
